prompt: What are the admission requirements for undergraduate programs at USF?
response:
Admission Requirements for Undergraduate Programs at USF:

• Submit an application for Florida Board of Governor’s Regulation 6.005 consideration [1]
   - Option 1: SAT, ACT or CLT scores and official transcript from a post-secondary/dual enrollment institution with Fall 2024 grades before admissions evaluation
   - Option 2: Florida A.A. Intent Form and an official transcript from the post-secondary/dual enrollment institution with Fall 2024 grades prior to admissions evaluation
• To be automatically considered for both admission options, submit both test scores and your post-secondary official transcript [1]
• Pay the $200 admissions deposit once admitted [1]
• Reserve and attend a freshman Orientation date [1]
• Submit your final official college transcript that displays completion and award of an A.A. degree before enrolling in classes [1]
• Finish all other next steps on the provided checklist after admission [1]
